parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the LED taillight assembly can cause the brake lights and taillights to malfunction or not work at all, leading to a safety hazard and potential accidents.
symptoms: The taillights or brake lights are inoperable
intermittent
or flickering; the lights may work sometimes and not work at other times; the lights may not illuminate when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The brake lights do not work consistently
may turn on and off randomly
or may not work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, as the trailer may not brake properly.
symptoms: The trailer brake system warning light comes on
the brakes do not engage
and the system may not function even when not towing a trailer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, as various systems may not function properly.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems
such as the infotainment system
instrument panel
and keyfob
may malfunction or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, as the vehicle may not shift gears properly.
symptoms: The clutch pedal may feel soft or spongy
the vehicle may not shift gears
or the transmission may fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blind spot monitoring system can cause accidents, as the driver may not be aware of vehicles in the blind spot.
symptoms: The blind spot monitoring system may not function
or the sensor may become detached from the rear bumper.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to difficulty stopping the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard to press
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the brake pedal feels spongy
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trailer brake system can cause the trailer to lose braking ability, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The "Service Trailer Brake System" warning light is illuminated
the trailer brake system is malfunctioning.
